    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 5.98,
      "end": 9.62,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 11.52,
      "end": 14.66,
      "text": "The Fox and the Monkey, an Asop's Fable.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 16.22,
      "end": 19.94,
      "text": "A Fox and a Monkey were on the road together and fell into dispute as to which of the two",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 19.94,
      "end": 20.68,
      "text": "was the better born.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 21.6,
      "end": 25.58,
      "text": "They kept it up for some time till they came to a place where the road passed through a",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 25.58,
      "end": 29.96,
      "text": "cemetery full of monuments when the Monkey stopped and looked about him and gave a great",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 29.96,
      "end": 30.24,
      "text": "sigh.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 31.46,
      "end": 33.38,
      "text": "\"'Why do you sigh?' said the Fox.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 34.16,
      "end": 36.18,
      "text": "The Monkey pointed to the tombs and replied.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 37.06,
      "end": 42.2,
      "text": "\"'All the monuments that you see here were put up in honor of my forefathers who in their",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 42.2,
      "end": 43.96,
      "text": "day were eminent men.'",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 44.72,
      "end": 48.3,
      "text": "The Fox was speechless for a moment, but quickly recovering he said,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 48.82,
      "end": 50.56,
      "text": "\"'Oh, don't stop at any lies, sir.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 50.96,
      "end": 51.7,
      "text": "You're quite safe.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-016",
      "start": 51.7,
      "end": 56.94,
      "text": "I'm sure none of your ancestors will rise up and expose you.'\"",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-017",
      "start": 56.94,
      "end": 57.28,
      "text": "The moral?",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-018",
      "start": 58.24,
      "end": 60.68,
      "text": "Boasters brag most when they cannot be detected.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-019",
      "start": 64.34,
      "end": 68.6,
      "text": "This has been an audio recording of the Fox and the Monkey from Asop's Fables, read by",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-020",
      "start": 68.6,
      "end": 72.5,
      "text": "Andy Fluke of 13pennies.net for LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
